HEADWORD: Cerris
<hw>Cer"ris</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cerrus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of oak
(<spn>Quercus cerris</spn>) native in the Orient and southern Europe; --
called also <altname>bitter oak</altname> and <altname>Turkey
oak</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

